<br /> <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yeah, sounds like they didn't hook the "CIRAM /CE" line up and PPU /A13 to the cart port, but instead connected those internally. They must not have known you had to do this for NES carts (though you still do for fami carts). </div>
<br />
<br />If they hooked the lines to the Famicom connector, then it is likely that these games would work if connected to a 60-72 Pin Converter, like the sort Lik Sang sell.  How ironic would that be?

		

